  "text": "Necessity of the radiocapitellar fixation is an another matter of debate in the treatment of Monteggia lesions. Although some authors advocate radiocapitellar fixation with the temporary Kirchner wire, some authors warn about a possible pin migration and osteoarthritic changes due to radiocapitellar pinning [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Delpont et al. [CITATION_4] suggested that if the radial head is unstable after the ulnar osteotomy, surgeons should consider revising ulna osteotomy in terms of radiocapitellar pinning [CITATION_5] . To achieve sta- ble radiocapitellar joint was possible after the ulnar osteotomy; therefore, we did not employed pinning.",
